@startuml Sequence Diagram - Leave Request Flow

actor Employee
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "LeaveController" as LC
participant "LeaveRequest" as LR
participant "Database" as DB
actor Admin

Employee -> Browser : Fill leave application form
Browser -> LC : POST /leave/apply
LC -> LC : Validate input
LC -> LR : create(status=pending)
LR -> DB : INSERT leave_requests
DB --> LR : saved
LR --> LC : LeaveRequest instance
LC --> Browser : Redirect with success
Browser --> Employee : Leave request submitted

note over DB : status = pending

Admin -> Browser : View pending requests
Browser -> LC : GET /admin/leaves
LC -> DB : SELECT pending requests
DB --> LC : results
LC --> Browser : Render list
Browser --> Admin : View requests

Admin -> Browser : Approve or Reject
Browser -> LC : POST /admin/leaves/{id}/update
LC -> DB : UPDATE status, reviewed_by, reviewed_at
DB --> LC : updated
LC --> Browser : Redirect with confirmation
Browser --> Admin : Request updated

Employee -> Browser : View leave history
Browser -> LC : GET /leave/history
LC -> DB : SELECT WHERE user_id = ?
DB --> LC : records
LC --> Browser : Render history
Browser --> Employee : View status

@enduml
